title: Follow live: Tennessee strikes first in showdown with Georgia
description: The No. 7 Vols have only one loss and hope to hand the No. 12 Bulldogs a third defeat tonight in Athens, Ga. Follow it all here, including No. 1 UO at Wisconsin.
author: Yahoo Sports
excerpt: There are two games between ranked opponents in Week 12 and both of those games are in the SEC.

html:
We've hit the home stretch of the 2024 college football regular season.

There are just three weeks to go before conference championship week in the first week of December. Week 12 isn't the most loaded slate, but it does feature plenty of matchups that could impact conference title races.

Here's what we're watching close late on Saturday. (Scroll down to follow the action live.)

Time: 7:30 p.m. ET | TV: NBC | Line: Oregon -14 | Total: 52.5

Is this the toughest game remaining on the Ducks’ regular-season schedule? We won’t get into tiebreakers here, but if Oregon wins Saturday night it will likely play the winner of next week’s game between Indiana and Ohio State in the Big Ten title game. Wisconsin enters the game on a two-game losing streak.

No. 7 Tennessee at No. 12 Georgia

Time: 7:30 p.m. ET | TV: ABC | Line: Georgia -10.5 | Total: 48.5

Vols QB Nico Iamaleava is reportedly set to play after going through the concussion protocol earlier in the week. Georgia is out of the College Football Playoff mix with a loss; the Vols’ visit on Saturday night gave the committee an easy out with its placement of the Bulldogs on Tuesday.

Kansas at No. 6 BYU

Time: 10:15 p.m. ET | TV: ESPN | Line: BYU -3 | Total: 56.5

Your eyes aren’t fooling you. The undefeated top-10 BYU Cougars are favored by just a field goal at home against a team that has a losing record. Overall, four of BYU’s nine wins have come by a single possession and Kansas just took down Iowa State in Week 11.

Live100 updates

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 7:12 PM CST

    Boise State gets on the board

    QB Maddux Madsen punches in Boise State's first points of the game. Broncos cut the San Jose State lead in half.

    San Jose State 14, Boise State 7 | 2nd quarter

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 7:09 PM CST

    ASU all over K-State

    No. 16 Kansas State is already in big trouble at home against Arizona State. Sam Leavitt has already thrown 3 TD passes for ASU.

    Arizona State 21, Kansas State 0 | 2nd quarter

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 7:02 PM CST

    Touchdown Tennessee!

    Tight end Miles Kitselman dives over the pile for the score, and the Vols strike first in Athens.

    Tennessee 7, Georgia 0

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 6:59 PM CST

    Wisconsin picks off Oregon!

    Nyzier Fourqurean intercepts Oregon QB Dillon Gabriel near the goal line.

    Big stop for the Badgers, who took points off the board with that one.

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 6:53 PM CST

    SJSU hammering Boise State early

    In surprising news, Boise State is in serious trouble early on the road at San Jose State.

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 6:51 PM CST

    Final: South Carolina 34, Missouri 30

    Fun game and exciting finish, and Missouri's last gasp of a playoff hope goes down the drain.

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 6:45 PM CST

    Touchdown South Carolina!

    LaNorris Sellers flips a shovel pass to Raheim Sanders, who rumbles 15 yards into the end zone.

    What a wild last few minutes this has been.

    South Carolina 34, Missouri 30 | 0:15 to play

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 6:43 PM CST

    South Carolina has calmly driven the ball into field goal range and inside the Mizzou 20.

    Under 30 seconds to play.

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 6:37 PM CST

    Mizzou takes the lead on a bomb TD!

    Brady Cook with an absolute DIME down the sideline to Luther Burden on 4th down, and Missouri is back in front.

    2-point try is good.

    Missouri 30, South Carolina 27 | 1:10 to play

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 6:30 PM CST

    USC hangs on to beat Nebraska

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 6:25 PM CST

    South Carolina retakes the lead

    LaNorris Sellers gets it to Michael Smith for a go-ahead 5-yard TD pass. 2PC is no good. 5:04 to play.

    South Carolina 27, Missouri 22

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 6:13 PM CST

    Stanford upsets No. 19 Louisville

    Unbelievable sequence at the end of the game. Louisville committed back-to-back penalties totaling 20 yards to get Stanford in field goal range, and the Emmet Kenney hit the 52-yard winner at the buzzer. That's a big upset with potential big implications in ACC tiebreakers

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 6:09 PM CST

    Final: SMU 38, Boston College 28

    No. 14 SMU survives the upset bid and gets to 9-1, 6-0 in ACC play. The Mustangs are still in prime position to make the ACC title game.

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 6:07 PM CST

    Final: Florida 27, LSU 16

    Florida gets to 5-5 with an upset over No. 22 LSU. Tigers (6-4) went from a playoff hopeful to a disappointing season in the span of a few weeks.

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 6:04 PM CST

    Touchdown Stanford!

    The Cardinal have tied things up in Palo Alto with a late touchdown from Emmett Mosley. They opted to go for the tie though, so Louisville still has a sliver of time left.

    Stanford 35, Louisville 35

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 6:00 PM CST

    BC turns it over on downs

    SMU sacks Grayson James on 3rd and 4th down and the drive ends before it really started.

    The Mustangs can run this one out.

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 5:55 PM CST

    Boston College has the ball at its own 31, trailing 31-28, at the 2-minute timeout.

    Can BC pull off the upset over No. 14 SMU?

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 5:52 PM CST

    Touchdown Florida!

    Jadan Baugh breaks free down the sideline for a 55-yard TD run, and that will just about put this away.

    Florida 27, LSU 16, 3:48 to play

  • Sat, November 16, 2024 at 5:50 PM CST

    USC kick blocked!

    The Trojans had a chance to take the lead in the fourth quarter but their field goal attempt has been blocked.
